The safest countries for tourists
.
.

The countries are: Norway, Finland, Iceland, Denmark (and Greenland), Slovenia, Switzerland, Luxembourg

The dangers of travel in these countries was ranked as insignificant. The US, Australia, New Zealand, Canada and most of Europe were rated as having a low level of travel risk. International SOS assigns travel medical risk ratings by assessing a range of health risks and mitigating factors, including but not limited to: infectious disease burden, environmental factors, medical evacuation data, road trauma data, standard of emergency medical services, outpatient and inpatient medical care, access to quality pharmaceutical supplies, and cultural, language or administrative barriers.
.
.
Source: InternationalSOS (2019)
